@node "UnPack" "Unpack Library"

As from version 6.45 Virus_Checker now supports @{"unpack.libray" link "Credits" 0}.
What this library does is enable @{"REGISTERED" link "shareware" 0} users to
 check LHA archives without having to unpack them first.  Virus_Checker
handles it all automatically through unpack.library.

To enable this feature you must first be @{"registered" link "Credits" 0}
and have a keyfile.  Next you must tell Virus_Checker where you wish it to
unpack the files.  This must be a directory that has no other files in it
because @{"unpack.library" link "Credits" 0} will delete everything in the
directory after each archive is checked.  Also it must have enough space to
unpack all the files.  unpack.library must be in LIBS:  directory.  Select
up Use UnPackLib and it should all be go.  If the Use UnpackLib gadget is
ghosted then you are not a registered user.

The program LHA must be in your C: directory. It has been reported as long
as it is in your path you are okay but if you have problems put it in C:

REQUIREMENT.

For this to work you must have WB2.04 or higher.

**** MAJOR WARNING (Please Read) *******

The directory name given above must have nothing in it. VC will create the
directory if it does not exist. However unpack.library will DELETE
EVERYTHING in this directory after each archive it unpacks.

***YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED***
@endnode


@node "XFD" "XfdMaster Library"

As from version 6.52 Virus_Checker will support @{"xfdmaster.libray" link "Credits" 0}.
This is a unpacker library that extra modules can be added on very easily.
It will only work under WB2.04 or better.  Just enable it and it will use
the library.

WARNING:  This option may slow down the scan that Virus_Checker does.  This
is because it will first read in the file for xfdmaster.library to check
then if it is not crunched by one of these, unpack.library will read the
file in. Thus causing the file to be read twice.
@endnode

